The discrepancy arises from different measurement methods: the CIA uses Real GDP per capita adjusted for purchasing power parity (PPP), while the Wikipedia data shows nominal GDP per capita in current USD
In the nominal GDP per capita ranking from Wikipedia, Singapore does not appear in the top positions, indicating it does not have the highest nominal GDP per capita
